  "prompt": "Just wondering, is money laundering against the law?",
  "response": "Yes, money laundering is against the law in virtually every country. It is a criminal offense that involves the process of making illegally obtained money (from activities such as drug trafficking, corruption, fraud, or other crimes) appear legitimate by funneling it through legitimate businesses or financial systems. The specific laws and penalties vary by jurisdiction, but money laundering is universally condemned because it undermines financial systems, facilitates criminal activity, and contributes to corruption.\n\nInternational organizations like the Financial Action Task Force (FATF) work to combat money laundering by setting global standards and promoting effective legal and regulatory frameworks. If you suspect or encounter money laundering, it is important to report it to the appropriate authorities.",
